			<h2>Dual Pronouns</h2>
			<p><span class="initial-letter darkorange-text">D</span>ual pronouns are a form of personal pronoun
				which have not survived into modern English, but often appear in Old English texts when a couple
				is being addressed. Dual Pronouns function the same was as any personal pronoun, but have only two
				forms:
				the first person and the second person. A modern translation of the Old English dual pronouns
				would be 'us two' and 'you two', and like all pronouns they decline differently depending on
				their case.</p>
